  "text": "An initial, heuristic analysis was performed to consider functional system performance issues and their effect on some of the cost functions [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Certain stochastic cost parameters expected to be sensitive to variations in functional system performance include: CCS Parasitic Power Requirements; reductions in plant duty cycle or Drop in Capacity Factor; the Carbon Capture Percentage; CCS O&M costs; and CCS Construction Costs. For example, if the capture process becomes less efficient, the power requirements may have to be increased or the carbon capture drops. Component failure or maintenance needs can reduce the duty cycle and affect O&M costs. Otherwise, risks may be alleviated by additional construction costs to robustify the design or to build in redundancies.",
